{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexRef"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/mutexprotocol"]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","title":"MutexProtocol","externalID":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Take for example the following function:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","","    \/\/ now do a very complicated calculation to calculate the new","    \/\/ number, this might for example be a random number generator","    current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","","    return current_number;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is easy to see that this won’t work in a multi-threaded"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application. There current_number must be protected against shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"access. A ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used as a solution to this problem:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static GMutex mutex;","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","","    g_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice that the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is not initialised to any particular value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Its placement in static storage ensures that it will be initialised"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to all-zeros, which is appropriate.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" is placed in other contexts (eg: embedded in a struct)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then it must be explicitly initialised using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_init()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":" should only be accessed via g_mutex_ functions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Methods","generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/lock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/trylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/unloc